---
alwaysApply: true
---

Apply to all implementation work without exception:

- Every task in the Plan corresponds to exactly one branch.
- Branch naming follows this pattern:
  task/[task-number]-[short-description]
  Examples: task/04-user-auth, task/07-dashboard-ui
- No code is ever written directly on main or dev.
- Always pull the latest dev before creating a new task branch.
- A task is not considered complete until its branch has been 
  reviewed, all tests pass, and it has been merged back to dev.
- PROJECT.md tracks branch name and merge status alongside 
  each task.
- Never merge a branch that has failing tests.
- Never merge a branch that has unresolved [REVISIT] markers.
- If a task branch reveals a conflict with another branch, 
  flag it immediately as a blocker before continuing.
- Commit messages must be specific and describe what was built.
  Never use "updates", "fixes", or "changes" alone as a message.
- Use --no-ff on all merges to preserve task history in the 
  branch graph.
